President Muhammadu Buhari (rtd) has appointed Deputy Commissioner of Police, Aliyu Musa, as his Chief Personal Security Officer. The Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, in a statement on Monday disclosed this, adding that Musa, who is from the Nigerian Police Force Zone 5, Benin City, hails from Niger State. According to Shehu, “Musa’s appointment follows the redeployment of his predecessor, Commissioner of Police, Abdulkarim Dauda.”